Bukele <a href="https://twitter.com/nayibbukele/status/1254672643745370113">tweeted</a> on Monday that he was meeting with his security cabinet and planned to make the gangs pay for the homicides.

President Bukele was recently criticized for <a href="https://www.jurist.org/news/2020/04/el-salvador-president-defies-supreme-court-order-on-covid-19-detention/">defying Supreme Court order concerning COVID-19 detention</a>.

El Salvador has also been under fire recently for extending its <a href="https://www.jurist.org/news/2020/04/el-salvador-extends-covid-19-state-of-emergency-law-despite-human-rights-concerns/">Covid-19 state of emergency law despite human rights concerns</a>.
